\f0\fs24 \cf0 There are large racial disparities in the murder data of Philadelphia. In June, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2018/investigations/unsolved-homicide-database/?utm_term=.cf98b281858f&city=philadelphia"}}{\fldrslt The Washington Post published}} a story analyzing the arrest record for murder cases in cities across the country. For this piece, I used the data collected by The Washington Post from the medical examiners office in Philadelphia. \
\
While the data was already well-maintained by the data team at WaPo, I had to do a little cleaning to remove some errant data from 2017 as well as some mis-categorized racial designations. After that, I was able to jump right in to analysis. \
\
