Philadelphia had around 3035 murders between 2007-2016. Philly P.D. closed 55% of those cases, while 45% of them resulted in no arrest. While African-Americans represent around 43% of the population of Philadelphia, about the same as whites, they represent about 78% of the murders. For white victims, only 23% of cases are unsolved, but for black victims that number raises to almost 44% \
